						<summary>

						<p>Eastern <hi rend="italic">gōpura</hi> (proper left) of Aruṇāchalēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>[Achyutadēvarāya]</p>						

						<p>This damaged record refers to the construction of a <hi rend="italic">gōpura</hi> by Chikka-Chevva of the family of Timma-bhūpāla, who is highly eulogised. He appears to have had the <hi rend="italic">gōpura</hi> of the temple at Aruṇapura constructed. The record refers to Achyutadēvarāya-mahārāya, the Vijayanagara king. It is undated. </p>						

						</summary>
